1
00:00:00,467 --> 00:00:03,933
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYS]

2
00:00:06,767 --> 00:00:08,333
<i>You're bypassing
the chain of command?</i>

3
00:00:08,333 --> 00:00:09,500
<i> Am I not your head agent?</i>

4
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:12,067
<i> I keep telling you!
We need to find Datu Rahman</i>

5
00:00:12,067 --> 00:00:15,267
<i>because that's the only reason
why Director Azuelo agreed</i>

6
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:17,333
to give you your position back!

7
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:19,233
<i> We need to find this bastard.</i>

8
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,700
<i> I want two million, too!</i>

9
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:22,533
<i> How can I help?</i>

10
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:23,967
<i> I need to get inside.</i>

11
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:28,333
<i>The people who attacked
our island are inside NLEA.</i>

12
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,667
<i>And that's where I can find
the answers I'm looking for.</i>

13
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:35,567
<i>Jamilah just started
in her new job.</i>

14
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,267
<i> I'm Jamilah.</i>

15
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> Welcome to the team, Jamilah.</i>

16
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>I hope you're strong enough.
You know how the ER is.</i>

17
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,867
<i> Don't worry, Doctor.</i>

18
00:00:43,867 --> 00:00:45,600
<i> I never give up.</i>

19
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:49,767
<i>I will never give up
on helping Jalil</i>

20
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,667
<i> and looking for my father.</i>

21
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:55,367
<i> will tell us where he is.</i>

22
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:56,833
<i> And you, Doctor,</i>

23
00:00:56,833 --> 00:01:00,367
<i>will be my way
to get closer to him.</i>

24
00:01:00,367 --> 00:01:02,867
<i> a gun smuggling operation.</i>

25
00:01:02,867 --> 00:01:05,533
<i>Someone's helping them out
from our side!</i>

26
00:01:05,533 --> 00:01:06,900
<i>Not only do they have
Datu Rahman,</i>

27
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,033
<i> they also know our every move.</i>

28
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:11,333
<i> We have an internal breach.</i>

29
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:14,333
<i>See, Marcus?
I'm always two steps ahead.</i>

30
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:17,033
<i>If you're wrong,
your career is over.</i>

31
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:19,367
<i> Our fight has only just begun.</i>

32
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:23,700
<i>Whoever you are
that's behind all this chaos...</i>

33
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:26,867
<i> I'm going to catch you.</i>

34
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:36,933
[THEME MUSIC PLAYS]

35
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:48,633
You told Director Azuelo
about your theory?

36
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:51,367
Isn't he one of your suspects?

37
00:01:52,567 --> 00:01:53,733
Yes.

38
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:56,867
But the last time we talked,
I confirmed he's clean.

39
00:01:57,400 --> 00:02:01,567
But he's still part of NLEA,
so I can't trust him completely.

40
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:05,000
You know what? You're right.

41
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:07,567
The people who took Datu Rahman,

42
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:10,033
I'm sure they know people
from the inside.

43
00:02:10,733 --> 00:02:11,867
Think about it.

44
00:02:11,867 --> 00:02:13,567
They got to him so fast.

45
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,600
Almost too perfect.

46
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:17,833
They've done so much
for Datu Rahman.

47
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:23,767
They massacred
the entire Damai Island

48
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:25,567
just to get him arrested.

49
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:29,133
Then, they kidnapped him
while he was being transferred.

50
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,733
And what did the media say?

51
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:33,533
They said he escaped.

52
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:38,833
Why Datu Rahman,
out of all people?

53
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:43,667
Why do they have to kill people
just for him?

54
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:47,767
And instead of killing him,

55
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,967
they just kidnapped him.

56
00:02:51,433 --> 00:02:52,600
[GRUNTING]

57
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:55,033
[GUNSHOTS]

58
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:03,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:25,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:03:41,033 --> 00:03:47,967
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

61
00:03:55,967 --> 00:03:57,933
They always know our every move.

62
00:03:58,533 --> 00:04:00,567
But even if they knew
we were coming,

63
00:04:00,567 --> 00:04:05,033
how were they able to hide
Datu Rahman that fast?

64
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:22,133
Ma'am.

65
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:26,500
[REPORTER 1]<i> Do we have any info
</i> on Datu Rahman's whereabouts?

66
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,600
<i>Did the syndicate
really let him escape?</i>

67
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:31,533
<i>Aren't you worried that
they might retaliate anytime?</i>

68
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:32,933
<i> What do you plan on doing?</i>

69
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:36,000
[REPORTER 2]<i> How about
</i> the victims on Damai Island?

70
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,533
Are we going
to deny them of justice?

71
00:04:39,667 --> 00:04:41,200
Agent Reyes is here.

72
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:43,867
Agent Reyes! Come over here.

73
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:47,700
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

74
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:50,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,000
<i> Agent Reyes.</i>

76
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:56,067
<i>I think they would love
to hear a word from you.</i>

77
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:01,467
- Sir, sir...
- Wait, wait.

78
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,433
Agent Reyes.

79
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:10,767
Are we correct to assume
that the SID is useless?

80
00:05:10,767 --> 00:05:14,933
No accountability and
no justice. Right, Agent Reyes?

81
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:22,567
[WOMAN 1] My god.
They killed innocent people

82
00:05:22,567 --> 00:05:24,233
just to arrest Datu Rahman?

83
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,800
And now, they let him escape.

84
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,100
Hello? Due process?

85
00:05:29,633 --> 00:05:32,033
Let's just wait
for the investigation first.

86
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:35,067
Due process? But Datu Rahman
is a real criminal.

87
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:36,300
[WOMAN 1] Yeah.

88
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:39,000
[WOMAN 2] But you know
who's also a criminal?

89
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:42,167
The leader of the group
who massacred an entire island.

90
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:43,900
Marcus Reyes!

91
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:45,333
Yeah, him, too.

92
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:47,600
Why don't you start
watching the news?

93
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:51,133
[JAMILAH]
<i> You, Agent Marcus Reyes.</i>

94
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:56,167
You are the leader of the group
<i> that killed our people.</i>

95
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:58,267
<i>You're the one
who arrested my father.</i>

96
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:02,900
<i>I will make you pay
for what you've done.</i>

97
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:08,300
Any updates on Datu Rahman?

98
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,933
Well, he's still
on the loose, sir.

99
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:15,667
He was held captive
at the Dapayan compound

100
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:17,333
before being transferred
to the ZylveriX.

101
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:21,333
[MARCUS] That was his
last known location.

102
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:25,000
As of now, we still don't know
where he's taken to.

103
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:29,600
This is outrageous!

104
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:38,067
<i> Clear.</i>

105
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:48,033
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,700
[MARCUS]
<i> How did you hide Datu Rahman?</i>

107
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:03,700
<i> And where did you take him?</i>

108
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:05,633
What do you think, Agent Reyes?

109
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,767
Do you have any leads
on Datu Rahman?

110
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:13,000
No leads, Agent Angeles.

111
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,233
Well, you better start
looking for one!

112
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:23,833
I expect you to submit
a progress report

113
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:26,000
before midnight!

114
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:32,967
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

115
00:07:37,233 --> 00:07:38,733
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

116
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,133
[DOOR OPENS AGGRESSIVELY]

117
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:44,733
[DOOR CLOSES AGGRESSIVELY]

118
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:58,933
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:20,033
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

120
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,400
[SEAT BELT UNBUCKLES]

121
00:08:28,167 --> 00:08:29,767
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

122
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:38,767
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

123
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,033
[THUDS]

124
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:45,767
- [STEPS LOUDLY]
- [TRACKER CRUNCHING]

125
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:52,033
[AGGRESSIVE TAPPING]

126
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,467
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

127
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:58,367
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

128
00:08:58,367 --> 00:09:05,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:13,167
[AGGRESSIVE TAPPING CONTINUES]

130
00:09:24,367 --> 00:09:25,833
- Sir.
- Sir.

131
00:09:28,867 --> 00:09:29,967
Vinluan.

132
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,133
Condecido. How are you two?

133
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:33,333
Quite alright, sir.

134
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:35,833
Uh... perfect, sir.

135
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:37,367
We were just talking about you.

136
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,467
What?

137
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:42,500
What do you mean?

138
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,833
Because, sir,

139
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,367
back when we were still
at the academy,

140
00:09:47,067 --> 00:09:48,267
we've always been
impressed by you.

141
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,767
You were a consistent
star student.

142
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:55,367
So them blaming you
for the escape of Datu Rahman,

143
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,067
we don't believe
that you're responsible for it.

144
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:05,400
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:06,833
Thank you.

146
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,200
Being a policeman is a vocation.

147
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:11,500
What you need to be one

148
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,500
is courage

149
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,333
and fortitude.

150
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,367
But if you are able to overcome

151
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:20,400
all the challenges
and hardships,

152
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,800
I'm certain

153
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:24,533
that you'll reach
greater heights.

154
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,533
Thank you, sir.

155
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:31,367
We'll remember that.

156
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:33,167
Thank you.

157
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,600
Sir.

158
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:37,067
Sir.

159
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:38,233
Col. Del Mundo.

160
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:45,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,567
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

162
00:11:06,467 --> 00:11:08,167
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

163
00:11:17,133 --> 00:11:18,567
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

164
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:25,367
[PHONE VIBRATING]

165
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:29,900
What?

166
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:33,267
Alright. I'll head over.

167
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:35,400
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

168
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:38,933
[JALIL WHISPERING] Rashid!

169
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,167
Rashid, what were you
about to do?!

170
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:45,167
[WHISPERING] Jalil?!

171
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,633
This jerk is pissing me off!

172
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,467
He's always tailing you!

173
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,167
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

174
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:57,200
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

175
00:11:57,200 --> 00:12:02,933
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

176
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,233
Just ignore him.

177
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,167
It'll just stir up more trouble.

178
00:12:07,167 --> 00:12:08,433
Good thing you're here.

179
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:10,900
Sir Omar doesn't want
to tell you where you are.

180
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,600
I wanted to tell you something.

181
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:14,500
Do you know ZylveriX?

182
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:17,733
I saw the policemen
who ambushed us here

183
00:12:17,733 --> 00:12:19,633
with Marcus Reyes.

184
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:21,700
<i> Thanks, sir!</i>

185
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,067
[VENDOR] Come again!

186
00:12:23,067 --> 00:12:30,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:12:30,033 --> 00:12:32,000
[CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

188
00:12:34,033 --> 00:12:36,133
- [CAR HORN HONKING]
- [TIRES SCREECHING]

189
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:37,267
[LARA] Stupid!

190
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:40,200
There were cars
that come and go.

191
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:46,633
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

192
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:50,533
[VAN ENGINE REVVING]

193
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:54,200
I'm not sure if this has
anything to do with your Father.

194
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:57,567
But I thought
it could be helpful.

195
00:12:57,767 --> 00:12:59,567
Thank you, Rashid.

196
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:02,100
Any information

197
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:04,033
that can potentially point
to Father's location,

198
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:06,233
I'll gladly take.

199
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:07,433
Thank you.

200
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:12,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

201
00:13:12,267 --> 00:13:19,233
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:13:27,467 --> 00:13:34,433
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,267
[USMAN] Brother,  got anything?

204
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:51,067
See anything?

205
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:55,367
For now, nothing.

206
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:57,800
[MARCUS] I'm sure someone's
on the lookout here.

207
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,400
I shouldn't expose myself.

208
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:07,600
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:14:10,667 --> 00:14:12,400
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

210
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:22,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

211
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:33,667
Are you also searching
for Father here?

212
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:45,867
[SUSPENSEFUL STING]

213
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:50,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

214
00:14:50,433 --> 00:14:57,400
[POLICE CAR SIREN WAILING]

215
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:01,400
- [HANDBRAKE THUDS]
- [CAR DOOR OPENS]

216
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,333
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

217
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,400
Bro, go check it out.

218
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,167
Someone might be using drugs.

219
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:18,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

220
00:15:22,567 --> 00:15:24,200
It's clear, bro.

221
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,233
Alright.

222
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:27,533
Let's finish our snack then.

223
00:15:30,533 --> 00:15:31,667
Alright, bro.

224
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:36,867
I'm hungry.

225
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:39,433
Who is that?

226
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:41,267
[TIRES SCREECH]

227
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:43,267
- Hey!
- [GUNSHOTS]

228
00:15:43,267 --> 00:15:45,433
[GUNSHOTS]

229
00:15:45,433 --> 00:15:46,400
[MARK GROANS]

230
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:56,233
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:57,400
Let's get out of here!

232
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,467
[DOORS CLOSE]

233
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:03,367
[TIRES SCREECH]

234
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:11,400
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:33,500
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:38,800
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

237
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,467
Really?

238
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:42,400
Huh? How is that possible?

239
00:16:42,433 --> 00:16:43,900
They're both dead?

240
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,433
Geez. Poor rookies.

241
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:49,500
- Unbelievable.
- We just talked yesterday!

242
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,300
- Just last night.
- Poor fellows.

243
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:52,300
[LOUD THUD]

244
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:54,433
What happened?

245
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:58,467
Sabdani, haven't you heard?

246
00:16:58,467 --> 00:17:01,467
Condecido and Vinluan
were killed!

247
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:05,200
<i>- Sir.
- Sir.</i>

248
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:10,433
What?

249
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:11,567
It hasn't been confirmed yet.

250
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:14,833
But the initial investigation
points to an ambush.

251
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:18,467
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

252
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:19,667
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

253
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:21,467
- Hilario!
- Sir?

254
00:17:21,467 --> 00:17:23,267
There's a CCTV camera
facing the road

255
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:25,667
where Condecido and Vinluan
were shot, right?

256
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:26,933
Yes, sir.

257
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:28,700
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

258
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:33,700
But the footage and files
are corrupted.

259
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,367
What?

260
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:36,333
What happened?

261
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,500
We don't know, sir.

262
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:41,033
We're still trying to
retrieve the corrupted files.

263
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:43,533
But I don't think
we'll be able to recover them.

264
00:17:43,533 --> 00:17:50,500
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:17:57,333 --> 00:18:04,300
[NEWS THEME MUSIC PLAYS]

266
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:09,300
[NEWS ANCHOR] Despite
Agent Marcus Reyes's pursuit

267
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,733
of the alleged syndicate leader
<i> Datu Rahman,</i>

268
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:14,300
authorities remain tight-lipped

269
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:17,533
<i> about what really happened
</i>to the victims on Damai Island.

270
00:18:19,667 --> 00:18:21,367
- [THUD, WATER SPLASHES]
- [TERESA EXCLAIMS]

271
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,667
Your murderer son
should be behind bars!

272
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:29,500
What kind of mother
raises a son to become a killer?

273
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,933
So many people died
because of your son!

274
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,767
- What is this nonsense?
- You're so cruel!

275
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:35,567
My son is not a murderer!

276
00:18:35,567 --> 00:18:37,567
- He is!
- He should pay for his crimes!

277
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:38,600
Hey, stop it!

278
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,567
- Stop making a scene!
- It's her son's fault!

279
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:41,933
- That's not true!
- Her son's a criminal!

280
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:43,600
- Let's go, Doc.
- That is not true!

281
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,933
The evidence says otherwise!

282
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:47,067
Don't you dare
say that about my son!

283
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:48,267
- He is a criminal!
- Back off!

284
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:50,700
- He is a criminal!
- Where are you going?!

285
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,000
- Shame on you!
- Come back here!

286
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:56,033
- He will pay for what he did!
- Your son's a murderer!

287
00:18:56,067 --> 00:18:57,933
- Shame on you!
- He's a monster!

288
00:18:57,933 --> 00:18:59,967
How do you sleep at night?!

289
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:02,033
- Shameless!
- Murderer!

290
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:17,733
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

291
00:19:17,733 --> 00:19:18,733
Marcus.

292
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,033
[LARA SIGHS]

293
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:27,533
[SIGHS] Look...

294
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:30,700
I know it's going to sound like
I'm breathing down your neck,

295
00:19:30,733 --> 00:19:33,833
but I need an update
on the progress

296
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:35,667
of your search for Datu Rahman.

297
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,100
[INHALES, SIGHS SOFTLY]

298
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:40,667
I get it, Lara, but...

299
00:19:40,667 --> 00:19:43,900
Right now,
all my leads are dead ends.

300
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,467
Okay. If you say so.

301
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,000
But remember,

302
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,400
with every second that passes,
your trail gets colder.

303
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,700
[SIGHS]
I'm doing everything I can.

304
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:57,100
[CAR KEYS CLATTER]

305
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,067
Oh.

306
00:19:58,067 --> 00:19:59,167
- [THUD]
- Ow.

307
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:01,933
Oh, sorry. Sorry, sorry.
Are you okay?

308
00:20:01,967 --> 00:20:04,000
- Are you alright?
- Yes. Are you alright?

309
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,100
- Sorry.
- Sorry, sorry.

310
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:06,700
I'll get it.

311
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:08,633
- Where'd it go?
- I got it.

312
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,600
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYS]

313
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:20,700
You okay?

314
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:27,667
[CURIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

315
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Are you okay?

316
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:32,133
What is that?

317
00:20:33,533 --> 00:20:35,900
Why does my car
have a GPS tracker?

318
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:39,467
Maybe your car
has one too, Marcus.

319
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:40,700
Lara, Lara.

320
00:20:41,733 --> 00:20:43,233
I found something like this
before.

321
00:20:43,233 --> 00:20:44,533
I destroyed it.

322
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,800
We have to be careful.

323
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,500
We don't know
who our enemy is.

324
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:50,833
[DEVICE CLATTERS]

325
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:52,067
[THUD]

326
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:57,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:20:57,467 --> 00:20:58,233
I agree.

328
00:20:58,233 --> 00:21:00,133
Who knows
who we're up against.

329
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:02,900
Thank you.

330
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,233
Sir!

331
00:21:04,233 --> 00:21:06,700
Madam!
Good morning!

332
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:08,100
Have you heard the news?

333
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:14,933
Condecido and Vinluan were
gunned down during their patrol.

334
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:16,933
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:19,500
No one's safe anymore.

336
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,767
We have to be extra careful.

337
00:21:20,767 --> 00:21:27,700
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

338
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:41,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

339
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:45,533
<i>I spotted Marcus Reyes
surveilling ZylveriX.</i>

340
00:21:45,533 --> 00:21:47,033
<i> It's too big to cover.</i>

341
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:49,100
<i> Don't worry, I'll help you.</i>

342
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,967
<i> I'll monitor it with you.</i>

343
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:52,700
<i>It's being treated
as a random attack,</i>

344
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:57,133
<i>with no evidence
of who's behind it.</i>

345
00:21:57,133 --> 00:21:59,633
<i>All of the CCTV footage
was wiped out.</i>

346
00:21:59,633 --> 00:22:01,133
<i> This was no accident.</i>

347
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:03,133
<i>How did they get
Datu Rahman out?</i>

348
00:22:03,133 --> 00:22:04,767
<i>How did they
slip past us like that?</i>

349
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:09,133
<i> What are you up to,
Marcus?</i>

350
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:11,767
<i> We need to lock down ZylveriX.</i>

351
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:15,867
<i>I think Datu Rahman
is still in there.</i>

352
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:17,267
<i> We need a win!</i>

353
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:18,933
<i>We're going back
to the ZylveriX building.</i>

354
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:22,833
<i>This is a full-scale search
for Datu Rahman.</i>

355
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:23,667
<i> Move!</i>

356
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:27,533
<i>Angeles, Reyes,
lead the search.</i>
